Brazil Sugar Ship Line-Up Drops by 8 Vessels, Williams Says

-- B y   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 
2011-07-28T08:32:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/brazil-sugar-ship-line-up-drops-by-8-vessels-williams-says.html
As many as 50 ships were waiting to
load sugar at  Brazil ’s ports in the Center South, the country’s
main producing region, 8 fewer than a week earlier, according to
data from shipping agency Williams Servicos Maritimos Ltda.  The vessels were waiting at the ports of Santos and
Paranagua to load about 1.66 million metric tons of the
sweetener as of yesterday. On July 20, 58 vessels were waiting
to load about 1.94 million tons, Williams Brasil data showed.  Sugar output in Brazil, the world’s largest producer and
exporter, climbed 2.6 percent to 2.58 million tons in the first
half of July, according to data from industry group Unica.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Isis Almeida in London at 
